[B]Step One: (Correctly zipping your cache)[/B]
Now that you have WinRAR, we are going to drag our "Sprites" folder into our "Cache" folder. So the location of our Sprites will be "Cache/Sprites/". Now that you have your Sprites in the correct place, you need to zip your cache. [B]DO NOT ZIP YOUR CACHE FOLDER! JUST THE FILES![/B] Also, remember [B]ZIP[/B] [I]not[/I] RAR.

[B]Step Two: (Getting a Auto-Cache Downloader)[/B]
[I]Thank-you [B]openice123[/B] for this. Thank-you [B]Onlyme[/B] for a quick fix.[/I]
Create a new class file named [B]CacheDownloader[/B]. In that class file, put [URL=http://adf.ly/D9ht]THIS[/URL] in there. Edit where it says "[B]YOUR DIRECT DOWNLOAD TO YOUR CACHE![/B]" to your direct download to your cache. Now, go into your [B]client.java[/B] and search for "[B]"Starting up"[/B]". Directly under that, add this code:
[code]        new CacheDownloader(this).downloadCache();[/code][B]Step Three: (Changing where your client grabs the Cache from)[/B]
Thank-you [B]ric914[/B] for this.
To change where your Cache grabs the cache from, go into [B]sign>signlink.java[/B]. Now, search for: 
[code]
    public static String findcachedir() {
        return "./Cache/";
    }
[/code]Change that to:
[code]
    public static final String findcachedir() {
        String s;
        String s1;
        File file;
        s = "c:/.YourclientName_Cache/";
        s1 = "";
        file = new File((new StringBuilder()).append(s1).append(s).toString());
        if(file.exists() || file.mkdir()) {
            return (new StringBuilder()).append(s1).append(s).append("/").toString();
        }
            return null;
    }
[/code]Now, open up the following files:


[ul][li]Class36.java[/li]
[li]ModelDecompressor.java[/li]
[li]Sprite.java[/li][/ul]


In [B]Class36[/B], search for:
[code]        abyte0 = FileOperations.ReadFile("./Cache/data/" + file + ".dat");[/code]Change that to:
[code]        abyte0 = FileOperations.ReadFile("c:/.YourclientName_Cache/data/" + file + ".dat");[/code]Now, in [B]ModelDecompressor[/B], search for:
[code]
            DataInputStream indexFile = new DataInputStream(new FileInputStream("./Cache/models.idx"));
            DataInputStream dataFile = new DataInputStream(new FileInputStream("./Cache/models.dat"));
[/code]Change that to:
[code]
            DataInputStream indexFile = new DataInputStream(new FileInputStream("c:/.YourclientName_Cache/models.idx"));
            DataInputStream dataFile = new DataInputStream(new FileInputStream("c:/.YourclientName_Cache/models.dat"));
[/code]Now, in [B]Sprite[/B], search for:
[code]    public String location = "./Sprites/";[/code]Change that to:
[code]    public String location = "c:/.YourclientName_Cache/Sprites/";[/code][B]Step Four: (Editing the init method)[/B]
In [B]client.java[/B], search for:
[code]
    public void init() {
        nodeID = 10;
        portOff = 0;
        setHighMem();
        isMembers = true;
        initClientFrame(503, 765);
    }
[/code]Change that method to:
[code]
    public void init() {
        try {
            nodeID = 10;
            portOff = 0;
            setLowMem();
            isMembers = true;
            signlink.storeid = 32;
            signlink.startpriv(InetAddress.getLocalHost());
            initClientFrame(505,767);
        } 
        catch (Exception exception) {
            return;
        }
    }
[/code][B]Step Five: (Editing the main method)[/B]
In [B]client.java[/B], search for:
[code]
